<div class="p text-right font-secondary"><a href="figure/ytab333-F1/" class="usa-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open in a new tab</a></div></figure><p>Dr. Moghadasi graduated in Medicine and Master of Science in Biomedical Sciences in 2011 and in Master of Epidemiology in 2014. In 2017, she defended her PhD thesis entitled: ‘Hereditary breast cancer and the clinical significance of variants in the BRCA1 and BRCA2 genes’. She currently works as a Clinical Geneticist and post-doctoral researcher.</p></section><section id="sec13"><h2 class="pmc_sec_title">Supplementary material</h2>
